Like the male in most characters, except for: frons broader, 0.24 X head width; 2 well developed proclinate fronto­orbital bristle; entire T 6 with narrow hind region and series of marginal bristles; spiracle 6 situated in membrane and 7 within the sclerite; T 8 divided in two broad and exposed plates, without setae; epiproct divided into two small plates, each one with 1 setae; ST 6 broader than ST 5 ; ST 7 with longer bristles in posterior region; ST 8 joined to ST 7 , with a sclerotized and setose posterior area with a little median anterior projection; membranous vaginal plate (
